 BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY

 TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE AUSTIN/SAN ANTONIO TX 1125 PM CDT SUN JUN 7 2020 

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY. THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT NETWORK. THE IRVING POLICE DEPARTMENT IS SEARCHING FOR SERENITY BERRY, BLACK, FEMALE, 7 MONTHS, 30 INCHES, 22 POUNDS, BLACK HAIR, BROWN EYES, WEARING DIAMOND STUD EARRINGS, AND A WHITE ONESIE. POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR JOCELYN NICOLE BRIDGES, BLACK, FEMALE, 35 YEARS OLD, 5 FEET 9 INCHES, 280 POUNDS, BRAIDED BLACK HAIR WITH BROWN HIGHLIGHTS, BLACK EYES, AND WEARING A MULTICOLORED SHIRT AND BLUE JEAN TIGHTS, IN CONNECTION WITH HER ABDUCTION. THE SUSPECT IS DRIVING A BLUE 2011 FORD FOCUS WITH TEXAS LICENSE PLATE NUMBER OF M G P 8 6 4 2. THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN IRVING, TEXAS. LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR IMMEDIATE DANGER. IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE IRVING POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 972-273-1010. NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS THE IRVING POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 972-721-3515. $$
